  <Docs>
    <summary>Extends design-time behavior for controls that implement the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.Part" /> abstract class.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.PartDesigner> class is the base class for many of the various designers in the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts> namespace, which provide visual representations of Web Parts controls at design time. The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.PartDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A> property is overridden to always return `true`, so <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.PartDesigner> will always render a copy of the associated control rather than the control itself.  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
    <block subset="none" type="overrides">
      <para>The <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.PartDesigner" /> class does not have a public constructor, so you cannot inherit from it directly outside the <see cref="N:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts" /> namespace. Instead, use <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartDesigner" />, <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.EditorPartDesigner" />, or <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.CatalogPartDesigner" />, which derive from <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.WebParts.PartDesigner" /> and provide the same functionality with a public constructor.</para>
    </block>
